As an example, John created a filter called 'jira bugs' and shared it with everybody. When I log in, I can find it by doing a simple search for the filter name. Then, when I'm still in that 'manage filters' tab I can favorite it (star) or click the 'subscribe' link to subscribe to it. (screenshot1)

But when I click on the filter and I'm viewing it in the issue nav, I still have the 'star' option in the top left corner, but there's no 'subscribe' link on the left. (screenshot2)

When John is viewing it, he does have a 'subscribe' link on the left. So, only the filter author has the 'subscribe' option when actually viewing the filter. (screenshot3)

