Sometimes people either forget to put a proper issue reference in their commit messages, or make a typo that makes a link incorrect (e.g. to an unrelated issue).

There should be a way to link a revision like that to an appropriate ticket in JIRA after the fact it was done, avoiding full reindex of repository, as it will take a long time, and is a much more frequent occurrence.

In addition, there should be a way to remove a certain revision from the "Source" tab, in case issue was mentioned by mistake.

