Documentation for configuring/running products to use SSL are not consistent across products.

This arose from a customer requesting that the JIRA SSL config page be updated with more details, similar to the FishEye equivalent. Quoting the customer:

{quote}
...
http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Running+JIRA+over+SSL+or+HTTPS "Import Certificate into the Trust-store" step is pretty vague when it comes to specifics, and should probably be updated to look a lot more like http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/FISHEYE/FishEye+SSL+Configuration, although it did not mention cloning to the alias, and relies on an external URL instead of including the information in the body of the Fisheye article.
...
{quote}

Can we look over all of the SSL docs to make sure they're providing consistent information?

